Beagrep is a fork of the beagle project. It aims to vastly enhance
grep(1) speed by using the beagle search engine to do a coarse
filtering first.

Beagrep is an indexing sub-system and search aggregator built on top of
the Lucene.Net indexer.

For general information on Beagrep, visit http://baohaojun.github.com/beagrep.html.

For help on compiling Beagrep, visit 
http://baohaojun.github.com/Beagrep_Getting_Started.html.

If you want to improve or fix Beagrep, please read the HACKING file.  

For the latest gossip, visit http://twitter.com/beagrep

